## Appendix A — verify report block

> Provenance
> - Authoritative paradigm: Böckeler "keep quality left" — a single deterministic sensor script invoked identically by editor hooks, pre-commit, and GitLab CI so no two sensors disagree about green
> - Investigation protocol: run `.harness/scripts/{{ script_shell }}/verify.sh` (lint · typecheck · tests · honesty); for critical paths apply mutation / critical-path coverage gates and a "first red then green" TDD trace check; never weaken a rule, threshold, or test to pass
> - Output form: per-stage pass/fail report; on failure MUST cite path:line and a concrete fix instruction (not "make it green") — exit code 0 = PASS, anything else = FAIL

```text
Verify — ⟨id⟩  (mode: fast | full)
- lint:      pass | fail (⟨n⟩ errors)
- typecheck: pass | fail (⟨n⟩ errors)
- tests:     pass | fail (⟨n⟩/⟨total⟩)
- honesty:   pass | fail (mutation / TDD trace / no-weakening)
VERDICT: green | red
```
